---
title: Paprika Beef & Yellow Rice Bowls with Pickled Red Onion
description: Our savory paprika blend brings bold flavors to ground pork sautéed with green pepper in a light and simple tomato sauce. Golden-hued turmeric rice soaks up all those hearty flavors, while pickled red onion adds a tangy, zingy crunch. Sprinkle with fresh parsley, and serve up this colorful weeknight-friendly meal in a quick 20 minutes.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66a7ce95b9d3dca06061204c-ac45c9e0.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66aa7d19915008628f446666-en-US.pdf
time required: 20 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 770 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 82 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 610 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/paprika-beef-and-yellow-rice-bowls-66aa7d19915008628f446666
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{2}, 1¼ cups water, @Turmeric{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings, use 2¼ cups water and 1/2 tsp turmeric. Be sure to measure the turmeric—we sent more!

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @Red Onion{1}.

> Use whole onion for 4 servings.

Core, deseed, and dice @Long Green Pepper{1} into 1/2-inch pieces. Roughly chop @Parsley{1/4%oz}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, @Red Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Cover tightly with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until onion is bright pink, ~{1%minute}. Set aside.

> Use 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Beef{10%oz}, green pepper, and @Savory Paprika Blend{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and almost cooked through, ~{4%minutes}.

Add @Tomato Paste{1} and 1/4 cup water; cook, stirring, until pork is cooked through and liquid has mostly evaporated, ~{30-60%seconds} more. Remove from heat.

> Swap in beef or turkey for pork. Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; divide between shallow #bowls{}. Top with pork and as much pickled onion (draining first) as you like. Garnish with parsley and serve.